The paper discusses the generation of hard satisfiable formulas for constraint satisfaction problems, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of incomplete algorithms such as WalkSAT, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper presents theoretical and experimental results, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
